    <section class="card">
      <h1>Help</h1>
      <p>
        Quick answers, troubleshooting, and contact. SafeShare cleans links locally in your browser.
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        Summary: <b>No uploads</b> · <b>No accounts</b> · <b>No logs by SafeShare</b>.
      </div>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <details open>
        <summary>What does SafeShare remove?</summary>
        <p>
          The free web app removes common tracking parameters such as <span class="mono">utm_*</span> and click IDs
          like <span class="mono">gclid</span>, <span class="mono">fbclid</span>, <span class="mono">msclkid</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Pro adds advanced controls (policies + audit + allowlist) for stricter, domain-specific rules.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Is SafeShare an anonymity tool?</summary>
        <p>
          No. It is a hygiene step before sharing: it removes tracking parameters from the URL.
          The destination website can still collect data once you open the page (server logs, cookies, scripts, accounts).
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Why can a cleaned link sometimes break?</summary>
        <p>
          Some parameters are functional (e.g. product IDs, filters, language settings, affiliate attribution, or session keys).
          If a cleaned link fails:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Try opening the original link first.</li>
          <li>Then try the cleaned link again.</li>
          <li>If only the cleaned link fails, a parameter was likely functional.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          In that case, use a more conservative approach or Pro (audit/allowlist) to keep necessary keys.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Does SafeShare store my links?</summary>
        <p>
          No. SafeShare does not upload your links for processing. The app may store small preferences locally in your browser.
          Optional “impact” counters store only totals (no URLs, no domains).
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I use it on iOS and Android?</summary>
        <p>
          SafeShare runs in the browser, so it works on mobile and desktop. Sharing availability depends on the browser.
          If the share dialog isn’t available, SafeShare can copy the cleaned link.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How do I contact you?</summary>
        <p id="contact">
          For support, directory questions, or corrections, write to:
          <span class="mono">listings@safesharepro.com</span>
        </p>
      </details>

